        "The SVC implementation in scikit-learn provides a C parameter which controls the flexibility of the model (Scikit-learn developers, 2024).\n",
        "\n",
        "A small value of C produces a simpler, more rigid boundary, while a large value produces a more complex one, that fits close to the training data.\n",
        "\n",
        "As with the depth parameter in Random Forest, there is a risk of overfitting at high values and underfitting at low values.\n",
        "\n",
        "In 6.2 section, the default value of `C=1` was used. But, here, a range of values is tested on Dataset C with `n_mfcc=13` to confirm whether `C=1` remains optimal."
