        "As the results show, every feature subgroup seems to be contributing to the final accuracy score, by progressively getting better.\n",
        "\n",
        "MFCCs by itself produce a validation accuracy of 0.1739. While this is better than random chance, it is not particularly promising and suggests that timbral information alone is not sufficient enough to distinguish between 8 different songs when lyrics are absent.\n",
        "\n",
        "Adding Chroma features improves the accuracy to 0.2919. This jump in accuracy confirms that the pitch content across frequency bands captures a substantial amount of identifying information that the MFCCs might have missed. The two features are capturing independent pieces of information, not just overlapping contents.\n",
        "\n",
        "Adding Power and Pitch features on top of those brings the accuracy to 0.3106, which is a further improvement. Thus confirming that these features also contribute information beyond what the spectral features are already capturing.\n",
        "\n",
        "Each feature subgroup adds something relevant, meaning that adding even more complex features could likely push performance further.\n",
        "\n",
        "This finding is distinct from the MFCC tuning in Section 6.3, as, instead of coefficient use, the ablation study looks at whether each feature type is contributing to its place."
